00:18:07,085 --> 00:18:09,478
I’ll be performing again with this very orchestra

266
00:18:09,503 --> 00:18:11,623
on my back at the Dome for a live show.

267
00:18:11,648 --> 00:18:13,436
He's going to lean toward Inoo-san.

268
00:18:15,491 --> 00:18:17,965
I’ll follow Inoo-san’s lead.

269
00:18:19,700 --> 00:18:21,175
we’ll go with A, please.

270
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:22,046
Heeey!

271
00:18:22,340 --> 00:18:23,655
Yes, that’s correct!

272
00:18:23,680 --> 00:18:25,695
Finally there is someone for room A!

273
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:26,540
Amazing.

274
00:18:27,070 --> 00:18:28,273
Seriously amazing.

275
00:18:28,340 --> 00:18:30,660
We finally have someone who got it right. Yes!

276
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:34,029
But Room A is still empty.

277
00:18:34,980 --> 00:18:37,599
Aaah, gangan-gaaan!

278
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:42,341
No one’s here, no one.

279
00:18:43,715 --> 00:18:45,524
They went over there!

280
00:18:47,149 --> 00:18:48,923
ha..

281
00:18:50,260 --> 00:18:52,685
They had a huge breakout after finishing runner-up at the M-1.

282
00:18:52,710 --> 00:18:55,567
The popular comedy duo, Batteries.

283
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:57,818
All right, here they come.

284
00:18:58,340 --> 00:18:59,841
Go, Batteries!

285
00:19:00,272 --> 00:19:05,895
I see all kinds of rhythm-based acts at the theater too,

286
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:09,423
but this is totally different from an orchestra.

287
00:19:09,448 --> 00:19:11,345
And the answer they’ve come up with is...

288
00:19:11,370 --> 00:19:12,120
One, two...

289
00:19:12,780 --> 00:19:13,440
B!

290
00:19:13,785 --> 00:19:16,505
What are you doing?!

291
00:19:16,831 --> 00:19:18,535
Seriously, what are you doing?!

292
00:19:18,560 --> 00:19:20,260
Batteries!

293
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:23,835
B was clearly more powerful, wasn’t it?

294
00:19:23,860 --> 00:19:25,304
Yeah, the strength of the sound,

295
00:19:25,380 --> 00:19:27,255
and also, when they pulled back,

296
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:30,235
the softer side of the dynamics felt deeper to me.

297
00:19:30,580 --> 00:19:31,704
Aaah...

298
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:34,471
You blew it, man.

299
00:19:34,960 --> 00:19:37,375
Aaah. Team Yoshimoto has lost three in a row.

300
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:39,318
They’re just rolling further and further downhill.

301
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:40,261
This is correct.

302
00:19:40,340 --> 00:19:41,277
Yes.

303
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:42,100
Good.

304
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:43,220
Good, good, good.

305
00:19:43,376 --> 00:19:45,817
(confident but wrong)

306
00:19:46,420 --> 00:19:47,682
What...

307
00:19:48,039 --> 00:19:49,725
Is it really that split?

308
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:50,807
Seriously?

309
00:19:51,220 --> 00:19:55,427
This is how Emiko and Yoshimi felt
(worried but correct)

310
00:19:56,334 --> 00:19:58,897
uun

311
00:19:59,041 --> 00:20:02,961
For the last pair, if they get this wrong, they’ll be out

312
00:20:03,060 --> 00:20:05,276
Fruit Chuck are right on the edge.

313
00:20:05,470 --> 00:20:06,288
All right, they’re up!

314
00:20:06,610 --> 00:20:08,140
Do your best!

315
00:20:08,190 --> 00:20:10,152
Chuck is here!

316
00:20:11,109 --> 00:20:14,112
I really like musicals and go see them a lot,

317
00:20:14,160 --> 00:20:17,190
so I’m pretty used to hearing orchestras.

318
00:20:17,215 --> 00:20:19,785
You really think that is going to get you through this?

319
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:23,649
Whoa, that got harsh all of a sudden.

320
00:20:31,959 --> 00:20:32,991
Haaah!

321
00:20:35,467 --> 00:20:37,720
We still don’t know yet.

322
00:20:37,744 --> 00:20:41,195
They were really careful, taking each note one by one,

323
00:20:41,220 --> 00:20:44,083
and I could feel that sense of, like, 'we’re going to play this properly.'

324
00:20:44,120 --> 00:20:47,179
You said earlier we should go with the minority next time.

325
00:20:47,204 --> 00:20:50,567
Like, your world just keeps going, 'whoa,' and opening up more and more.

326
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:51,950
Like it just keeps expanding.

327
00:20:52,485 --> 00:20:55,020
Okay, it's B then

328
00:20:55,640 --> 00:20:56,695
We good with this now?

329
00:20:56,720 --> 00:20:57,638
Alright, last one.

330
00:20:57,712 --> 00:20:58,400
Ready, and...

331
00:20:58,660 --> 00:20:59,884
B!

332
00:21:02,914 --> 00:21:04,548
We don't want to disappear...

333
00:21:04,646 --> 00:21:06,971
(not worth showing)

334
00:21:07,694 --> 00:21:09,622
Ah, wait, we're already finished?

335
00:21:09,647 --> 00:21:11,329
FRUITS ZIPPER...

336
00:21:11,457 --> 00:21:12,877
Dum

337
00:21:12,902 --> 00:21:13,850
They disappeared.

338
00:21:13,889 --> 00:21:17,793
(not worth showing)

339
00:21:17,818 --> 00:21:20,877
They vanished with one question still left.

340
00:21:20,904 --> 00:21:24,475
In place of those unlucky idols, from here on...

341
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:28,280
Hollywood Zakoshisho will take on the big role with his over-the-top style.

342
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:30,788
We will not disappear.

343
00:21:32,518 --> 00:21:35,027
Good! They won't disappear!

344
00:21:35,482 --> 00:21:40,899
(disappointed but correct)

345
00:21:42,180 --> 00:21:46,106
For real?

346
00:21:46,569 --> 00:21:49,920
Fateful crossroads: time for the results.

347
00:21:51,759 --> 00:21:54,760
FRUITS ZIPPER has already disappeared once, but...

348
00:21:55,230 --> 00:21:59,851
Please enjoy their real nervous expressions on their actual faces.

349
00:22:00,095 --> 00:22:02,727
Alright, here we are.

350
00:22:03,155 --> 00:22:04,342
Please!

351
00:22:04,461 --> 00:22:06,216
Please come!

352
00:22:06,358 --> 00:22:08,434
Come on!

353
00:22:10,340 --> 00:22:12,347
The correct answer is...

354
00:22:15,841 --> 00:22:18,537
(useless prayers)

355
00:22:26,896 --> 00:22:29,303
I can still perform tomorrow!

356
00:22:33,019 --> 00:22:35,354
I can still perform tomorrow!

357
00:22:44,397 --> 00:22:46,898
(disappear) (not worth showing)

358
00:22:47,854 --> 00:22:50,669
Sen-chan's face!

359
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:55,646
Mr. Takahashi is the only one who nailed the A-correct answer.

360
00:22:58,056 --> 00:23:02,561
B people watching this on the monitor: please go to the ear doctor tomorrow morning.

361
00:23:04,551 --> 00:23:05,927
Amazing.

362
00:23:07,402 --> 00:23:14,993
Will GACKT-sama keep choosing correctly, even on a question that almost everyone got wrong?

363
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:22,773
The fateful crossroads: GACKT's answer revealed.

364
00:23:23,760 --> 00:23:24,809
Alright.

365
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:29,207
Here we go. Is Gaku-chan over there?

366
00:23:31,686 --> 00:23:33,378
Oh he's here!

367
00:23:33,420 --> 00:23:34,608
Yes!

368
00:23:36,780 --> 00:23:37,960
Oh he's here!

369
00:23:38,260 --> 00:23:39,482
Yes!

370
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:43,610
He really is there.

371
00:23:44,389 --> 00:23:45,557
Incredible.

372
00:23:45,825 --> 00:23:47,426
That's amazing!

373
00:23:47,847 --> 00:23:49,480
This one...

374
00:23:49,835 --> 00:23:51,797
It was really tough.

375
00:23:51,822 --> 00:23:55,634
Both options were insanely high level.

376
00:23:55,794 --> 00:23:58,560
Even while grumbling about how hard it was,

377
00:23:58,660 --> 00:24:00,700
he gave us his biggest victory pose of the day.

378
00:24:00,780 --> 00:24:02,808
An impressive 86 straight wins.

379
00:24:03,266 --> 00:24:05,191
With the final question still ahead,

380
00:24:05,320 --> 00:24:07,475
FRUITS ZIPPER have gone completely cold.

381
00:24:07,499 --> 00:24:09,139
Reflect on what you've done.

382
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:12,484
And after this, a huge twist is waiting.

383
00:24:12,585 --> 00:24:14,586
Alright, everyone who got it right,

384
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:19,958
These three chose the professional orchestra.

385
00:24:21,860 --> 00:24:23,560
And now, everyone who got it wrong, come on out.

386
00:24:24,129 --> 00:24:25,900
Here come the losers.

387
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:31,403
Oh, we've got a keyboard harmonica coming out.

388
00:24:33,672 --> 00:24:35,469
Even with a keyboard harmonica,

389
00:24:35,494 --> 00:24:37,510
they're totally being made fun of.

390
00:24:41,180 --> 00:24:43,560
Here come the ones who got it wrong.

391
00:24:45,060 --> 00:24:46,200
Okay, okay, okay.

392
00:24:50,021 --> 00:24:52,895
We started with eight groups,

393
00:24:52,920 --> 00:24:54,343
but take a look now.

394
00:24:54,368 --> 00:24:56,428
One group is gone

395
00:24:56,595 --> 00:24:58,595
Hamada-san

396
00:24:58,680 --> 00:25:00,699
Oh, they're saying something.

397
00:25:02,634 --> 00:25:04,112
Here is your last test.

398
00:25:04,137 --> 00:25:07,606
Check 6: Shabu-shabu.

399
00:25:07,820 --> 00:25:10,976
(I wanted to eat!)

400
00:25:11,001 --> 00:25:12,611
So noisy...

401
00:25:12,636 --> 00:25:19,618
This time, you'll be judging top-class shabu-shabu made with A-rank Yonezawa beef.

402
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:22,003
The final test:

403
00:25:22,084 --> 00:25:23,355
shabu-shabu.

404
00:25:23,809 --> 00:25:30,128
Hiyama, a long-established restaurant in Ningyocho, Tokyo, with over 100 years of history.

405
00:25:30,153 --> 00:25:35,033
Also famed for sukiyaki, it has held a Michelin one-star rating for 10 years straight.

406
00:25:35,518 --> 00:25:39,395
Hiyama, which knows everything about the charms of Yonezawa beef,

407
00:25:39,420 --> 00:25:45,277
shabu-shabu specially sliced premium loin, cut to the perfect thinness, in a secret dashi broth.

408
00:25:45,849 --> 00:25:51,080
The sesame sauce carries a refined aroma of freshly roasted and ground sesame.

409
00:25:51,140 --> 00:25:56,888
It brings out the natural sweetness of the meat even more.

410
00:25:57,200 --> 00:26:03,828
The final question is a three-choice quiz: A, B, or C.

411
00:26:03,853 --> 00:26:06,431
But this time, there are technically no wrong answers.

412
00:26:07,230 --> 00:26:08,508
What that means is...

413
00:26:08,533 --> 00:26:12,440
the other two choices are both things that would absolutely never happen.

414
00:26:12,618 --> 00:26:15,171
Whichever of those you pick, at that moment,

415
00:26:15,198 --> 00:26:18,543
no matter what rank you are, you disappear instantly.

416
00:26:18,568 --> 00:26:20,312
Whaaat?!

417
00:26:20,711 --> 00:26:21,532
No way!

418
00:26:21,660 --> 00:26:23,014
But we've worked so hard to get this far!

419
00:26:23,039 --> 00:26:25,080
Unless you choose the correct answer,

420
00:26:25,100 --> 00:26:26,155
you'll be gone!

421
00:26:26,180 --> 00:26:28,987
Alright everyone, here is the first absolutely impossible choice.

422
00:26:29,072 --> 00:26:31,298
It's pork.

423
00:26:31,356 --> 00:26:33,195
"Bu Bu" (oink oink) pig.

424
00:26:33,220 --> 00:26:34,314
This is not beef, you know.

425
00:26:34,340 --> 00:26:37,286
There’s no way you'll mess that up.

426
00:26:37,379 --> 00:26:40,334
And here’s the other one that is absolutely impossible.

427
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:42,756
Wild boar.

428
00:26:42,958 --> 00:26:46,004
Definitely I'd recognize

429
00:26:46,377 --> 00:26:48,773
Botan-nabe (boar) is really famous, of course,

430
00:26:48,798 --> 00:26:50,695
but the difference from beef

431
00:26:50,720 --> 00:26:52,177
is obvious.

432
00:26:52,358 --> 00:26:54,446
Now I’ll announce the representatives.

433
00:26:54,471 --> 00:26:57,337
From Team 86 Wins in a Row, we have GACKT-sama.

434
00:26:57,362 --> 00:26:59,317
Thanks for stepping up.

435
00:26:59,342 --> 00:27:01,315
From Team Anniversary,

436
00:27:01,340 --> 00:27:04,155
Hiromi Go-kun.

437
00:27:04,180 --> 00:27:06,220
From Team 50-Minute Lover,

438
00:27:06,244 --> 00:27:09,095
Megumi Ino-kun and Futo Kimura-chan.

439
00:27:09,120 --> 00:27:10,376
We’re counting on you.

440
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:12,260
From Team Kis-My-Ft2,

441
00:27:12,284 --> 00:27:17,177
Fujitani-kun, Tamamori-kun, and Senga-kun.

442
00:27:17,202 --> 00:27:21,195
From Team Emiko Tendo, we have Yoshimi Tendo.

443
00:27:21,220 --> 00:27:22,859
Please do your best.

444
00:27:24,209 --> 00:27:29,300
From Team Reunion with Okome no Onna, we have Ryoma Takeuchi.

445
00:27:30,915 --> 00:27:33,901
From Team Yoshimoto: Atsushi.

446
00:27:33,926 --> 00:27:36,635
only first name eh?

447
00:27:37,255 --> 00:27:39,513
You’ll either still be on screen at the end or you’ll vanish.

448
00:27:39,538 --> 00:27:40,692
Alright, let’s do this.

449
00:27:45,246 --> 00:27:46,796
Okay, let’s go.

450
00:27:49,133 --> 00:27:51,221
Wha...kettle and water

451
00:27:51,259 --> 00:27:53,259
That's terrible

452
00:27:53,747 --> 00:27:56,076
GACKT-san, does you drink have gold flake?

453
00:27:56,130 --> 00:27:58,130
Yes...

454
00:27:58,710 --> 00:28:04,758
Now we’ll reveal the correct answer here to everyone in the studio.

455
00:28:04,783 --> 00:28:06,885
Because there's only one answer right?

456
00:28:06,910 --> 00:28:08,321
The correct answer is...

457
00:28:08,860 --> 00:28:09,654
B.

458
00:28:10,722 --> 00:28:12,230
Only this is correct

459
00:28:12,524 --> 00:28:15,729
And now, final question

460
00:28:15,753 --> 00:28:17,429
start!

461
00:28:17,508 --> 00:28:20,716
The first one to be checked is...

462
00:28:20,834 --> 00:28:22,427
here he comes

463
00:28:24,266 --> 00:28:28,139
third-rate actor Ryoma Takeuchi.

464
00:28:28,164 --> 00:28:31,910
You’d never think anyone would actually say it’s wild boar, right?

465
00:28:32,540 --> 00:28:34,012
Yeah, exactly.

466
00:28:34,973 --> 00:28:39,277
But just in case, let’s have him plug his show first.

467
00:28:39,309 --> 00:28:43,420
The first love my character, a detective, reunites with after 23 years

468
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:45,240
turns out to be a suspect in a murder case.

469
00:28:45,538 --> 00:28:49,981
The feelings of caring for someone dear lead to an unexpected truth.

470
00:28:50,006 --> 00:28:51,440
It’s a human love mystery.

471
00:28:51,910 --> 00:28:55,694
The drama premieres on the 13th, Tuesday at 9 p.m.

472
00:28:55,830 --> 00:28:57,510
Please be sure to watch.

473
00:28:57,535 --> 00:29:00,393
It's OK. You're going to be OK.

474
00:29:00,580 --> 00:29:04,676
She might get dragged down with him, so I'll go ahead and do her promo too.

475
00:29:04,701 --> 00:29:08,934
Set in the Tokyo Regional Taxation Bureau, with Nanako Matsushima facing all kinds of trials,

476
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:12,481
and me playing one of the very quirky tax investigators,

477
00:29:12,577 --> 00:29:20,240
it’s a refreshing new drama where we take down sly, nasty tax evaders one after another.

478
00:29:21,080 --> 00:29:24,483
'Okome no Onna' starts January 8.

479
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:29,360
It airs Thursdays at 9 p.m., just like 'Doctor X' and 'Emergency Interrogation Room.'

480
00:29:29,890 --> 00:29:31,136
Don’t miss it.

481
00:29:31,161 --> 00:29:35,798
First up, the pork shabu-shabu that’ll knock you out in one go.

482
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:39,110
You can tell what this is right away.

483
00:29:41,279 --> 00:29:44,800
Here he's eating the correct one, Yonezawa beef.

484
00:29:44,800 --> 00:29:46,074
This right here, this is the correct answer.

485
00:29:46,099 --> 00:29:49,730
If you don’t pick this beef, you’ll disappear instantly.

486
00:29:49,842 --> 00:29:54,211
And if you pick this wild boar meat, you’ll vanish too.

487
00:29:54,680 --> 00:29:57,263
If someone chose this, it’d be hilarious though.

488
00:29:57,424 --> 00:29:58,096
Okay.

489
00:29:58,121 --> 00:29:59,401
He looks confident

490
00:29:59,426 --> 00:30:00,265
Easy

491
00:30:00,290 --> 00:30:02,712
For the ending payoff, B is the only choice.

492
00:30:03,580 --> 00:30:04,740
So he's going with B?

493
00:30:05,500 --> 00:30:06,444
Yes.

494
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:08,541
Nice, that was quick.

495
00:30:09,440 --> 00:30:11,154
So cool.

496
00:30:12,520 --> 00:30:14,312
The beef can only be B.

497
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:16,189
There’s no way you wouldn’t know that.

498
00:30:16,214 --> 00:30:19,984
A is probably pork and C is wild boar.

499
00:30:20,009 --> 00:30:22,187
He managed to stay on screen.

500
00:30:22,733 --> 00:30:27,425
Takeuchi nailed the final question perfectly.

501
00:30:27,720 --> 00:30:30,363
But someone who mixes up pork or wild boar with beef...

502
00:30:30,440 --> 00:30:31,738
There’s just no way, right?

503
00:30:31,998 --> 00:30:34,666
I’m sure I’ve got this one right.

504
00:30:34,752 --> 00:30:36,201
Next up,

505
00:30:37,320 --> 00:30:39,226
it’s Atsu-san

506
00:30:39,803 --> 00:30:43,335
Team Yoshimoto has been tumbling further and further down.

507
00:30:43,360 --> 00:30:45,610
Can they stop the slide?

508
00:30:45,760 --> 00:30:47,176
Please...

509
00:30:47,201 --> 00:30:48,743
Save us in the year-end closing!

510
00:30:48,900 --> 00:30:49,703
We’re counting on you, Atsushi.

511
00:30:49,728 --> 00:30:51,395
This one’s easy.

512
00:30:51,420 --> 00:30:54,085
Nothing feels off.

513
00:30:54,440 --> 00:30:56,254
Is the difference really that tiny?

514
00:30:57,140 --> 00:31:02,122
In the Michelin check, Atsushi nailed it solo.

515
00:31:03,240 --> 00:31:04,717
Show us how cool you can be.

516
00:31:04,818 --> 00:31:11,917
He mainly cooks for himself and has strong opinions when it comes to food.

517
00:31:12,579 --> 00:31:19,133
As the team’s senior member, he can’t make a mistake at the end and disappear.

518
00:31:27,546 --> 00:31:31,950
If he doesn’t pick the correct answer, B, he’s gone.

519
00:31:32,300 --> 00:31:33,279
The correct answer is

520
00:31:33,291 --> 00:31:34,759
A.

521
00:31:36,744 --> 00:31:39,430
(not worth showing)

522
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:53,211
Oh no, then that means it was pork!

523
00:31:54,938 --> 00:31:57,682
They're not coming...

524
00:31:57,707 --> 00:32:05,665
B and C didn’t have beef-like fibers, and A had way more sweetness, so...

525
00:32:05,690 --> 00:32:09,900
Come on, he goes to shabu-shabu restaurants all the time

526
00:32:11,060 --> 00:32:12,860
Alright, Batteries, bang!

527
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:14,472
